a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:2:"id";s:6:"ztds2t";s:4:"name";s:4:"code";s:6:"parent";i:0;s:8:"children";a:0:{}s:8:"settings";a:6:{s:11:"executeCode";b:1;s:9:"signature";s:32:"2d00d4f413ca09e88959beae6d360032";s:7:"user_id";i:1;s:4:"time";i:1772251117;s:4:"code";s:6221:"<!-- ============================================================
     SAMOTICS DETECTION STORY — Bricks Code Element
     URL: /proof/cavitation-centrifugal-pump
     Paste each section into the matching tab:
       1. PHP & HTML  →  the markup below
       2. CSS          →  detection-story.css
       3. JavaScript   →  detection-story.js
     ============================================================ -->


<!-- ===================== PHP & HTML ===================== -->

<main id="main-content" class="sam-detect">

  <!-- ─── 1. HERO (compact dark banner) ─── -->
  <section class="sam-hero sam-hero--detect">
    <div class="sam-hero__overlay"></div>
    <div class="sam-hero__inner">
      <div class="sam-hero__content">
        <p class="sam-hero__overline">Fault detection</p>
        <h1 class="sam-hero__h1">Process insights prevent long-term damage to 200 kW centrifugal pump</h1>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ─── 2. DETECTION SUMMARY BAR ─── -->
  <section class="sam-detect-summary">
    <div class="sam-detect-summary__inner">
      <div class="sam-detect-summary__grid">
        <div class="sam-detect-summary__item">
          <span class="sam-detect-summary__label">Asset</span>
          <span class="sam-detect-summary__value">Centrifugal product pump (200 kW, VFD-controlled)</span>
        </div>
        <div class="sam-detect-summary__item">
          <span class="sam-detect-summary__label">Fault detected</span>
          <span class="sam-detect-summary__value">Cavitation from suboptimal startup procedure</span>
        </div>
        <div class="sam-detect-summary__item">
          <span class="sam-detect-summary__label">Industry</span>
          <span class="sam-detect-summary__value">Chemical manufacturing</span>
        </div>
        <div class="sam-detect-summary__item sam-detect-summary__item--highlight">
          <span class="sam-detect-summary__label">Root cause</span>
          <span class="sam-detect-summary__value kpi-value">Operating procedure fixed</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ─── 3. THE STORY ─── -->
  <section class="sam-detect-story">
    <div class="sam-detect-story__inner">
      <div class="sam-detect-story__block">
        <p class="overline">The situation</p>
        <h2>What was at stake</h2>
        <p class="sam-detect-story__text">A 200 kW VFD-controlled centrifugal product pump was being ramped up to high speed at startup, even when the fluid level in the tank was very low. The mismatch between available NPSH and pump RPM induced severe cavitation — damaging the impeller, bearings, and mechanical seal with every occurrence.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="sam-detect-story__block">
        <p class="overline">What SAM4 detected</p>
        <h2>The signal and the diagnosis</h2>
        <p class="sam-detect-story__text">SAM4 flagged a sudden and significant rise in the noise floor around the pump's supply frequency — indicative of cavitation. Samotics alerted the customer, who inspected the pump and reviewed the records of that pumping session. They discovered the pump's speed had been rapidly ramped up while the tank level was too low for the positive displacement stripping pump to take over. The root cause was not a mechanical fault but a suboptimal startup procedure.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="sam-detect-story__block">
        <p class="overline">The outcome</p>
        <h2>What happened next</h2>
        <p class="sam-detect-story__text">The customer changed the operating procedure to match the product pump's speed at startup to the tank's current condition. This eliminated a recurring source of impeller, bearing, and seal damage across this and other centrifugal product pumps. SAM4 did not just detect a fault — it provided the insight needed to identify and fix the underlying process issue.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ─── CTA BLOCK ─── -->
  <section class="sam-cta-block sam-cta-block--detect">
