     SAMOTICS DETECTION STORY — Bricks Code Element
     URL: /proof/synthetic-fiber-production
     Paste each section into the matching tab:
       1. PHP & HTML  →  the markup below
       2. CSS          →  detection-story.css
       3. JavaScript   →  detection-story.js
     ============================================================ -->


<!-- ===================== PHP & HTML ===================== -->

<main id="main-content" class="sam-detect">

  <!-- ─── 1. HERO (compact dark banner) ─── -->
  <section class="sam-hero sam-hero--detect">
    <div class="sam-hero__overlay"></div>
    <div class="sam-hero__inner">
      <div class="sam-hero__content">
        <p class="sam-hero__overline">Product use case</p>
        <h1 class="sam-hero__h1">Preventing failure in synthetic fiber production</h1>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ─── 2. DETECTION SUMMARY BAR ─── -->
  <section class="sam-detect-summary">
    <div class="sam-detect-summary__inner">
      <div class="sam-detect-summary__grid">
        <div class="sam-detect-summary__item">
          <span class="sam-detect-summary__label">Asset</span>
          <span class="sam-detect-summary__value">Heated godet roll</span>
        </div>
        <div class="sam-detect-summary__item">
          <span class="sam-detect-summary__label">Fault detected</span>
          <span class="sam-detect-summary__value">Motor overloading</span>
        </div>
        <div class="sam-detect-summary__item">
          <span class="sam-detect-summary__label">Industry</span>
          <span class="sam-detect-summary__value">Synthetic fibre manufacturing</span>
        </div>
        <div class="sam-detect-summary__item sam-detect-summary__item--highlight">
          <span class="sam-detect-summary__label">Savings per detection</span>
          <span class="sam-detect-summary__value kpi-value">$90,000</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ─── 3. THE STORY ─── -->
  <section class="sam-detect-story">
    <div class="sam-detect-story__inner">
      <div class="sam-detect-story__block">
        <p class="overline">The situation</p>
        <h2>What was at stake</h2>
        <p class="sam-detect-story__text">Godet rolls are essential in synthetic fibre production — they heat-treat yarn at extremely high temperatures. If a roll fails, the entire production line shuts down for emergency repairs that can take hours. Traditional sensors melt or break in these conditions. Vibration sensors cannot work on slow-rotating rolls. And the assets cannot be approached by maintenance staff while running.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="sam-detect-story__block">
        <p class="overline">What SAM4 detected</p>
        <h2>The signal and the diagnosis</h2>
        <p class="sam-detect-story__text">SAM4 monitors from the motor control cabinet — far from the extreme temperatures. Its algorithms detected that the motor driving a heated roll was overloading: amperage levels exceeded the motor's rated current. The system immediately sent an alert, advising the customer to inspect the motor for signs of overheating and check insulation integrity. Within 30 minutes, the maintenance team inspected the motor and adjusted the tension on the roll. SAM4 confirmed the roll was operating healthily again.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="sam-detect-story__block">
        <p class="overline">The outcome</p>
        <h2>What happened next</h2>
        <p class="sam-detect-story__text">The customer reported that $90,000 in downtime costs were avoided. If the roll had failed during service, it would have caused 12 hours of downtime: $70,000 in lost production plus $20,000 in corrective maintenance. The timely warning made it possible to inspect and adjust the asset without shutting down the line. Across 14 rolls on one production line, the estimated annual profit from SAM4 monitoring is $283,500.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ─── CTA BLOCK ─── -->
  <section class="sam-cta-block sam-cta-block--detect">
    <div class="sam-cta-block__inner">
      <h2 class="sam-cta-block__heading">See what SAM4 can detect on your assets</h2>
      <p class="sam-cta-block__sub">Every detection story above comes from a real deployment. Request a demo to see how SAM4 works on your equipment.</p>
      <div class="sam-cta-block__actions">
        <a href="/contact?intent=demo" class="sam-btn sam-btn--primary">Request a Demo</a>
        <a href="/proof" class="sam-btn sam-btn--outline">See All Proof</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ─── RELATED DETECTION STORIES ─── -->
  <section class="sam-detect-related">
    <div class="sam-detect-related__inner">
      <p class="overline">Related detection stories</p>
      <h2>More results from the field</h2>

      <div class="sam-detect-related__grid">
        <a href="/proof/nyrstar" class="sam-detect-related__card">
          <span class="sam-detect-related__card-industry">Metals &amp; Mining</span>
          <h3 class="sam-detect-related__card-title">Nyrstar</h3>
          <p class="sam-detect-related__card-outcome kpi-value">800% ROI in 11 months</p>
          <span class="sam-detect-related__card-link">Read story &rarr;</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/proof/bearing-failure-motor-roll" class="sam-detect-related__card">
          <span class="sam-detect-related__card-industry">Steel</span>
          <h3 class="sam-detect-related__card-title">Bearing failure in motor roll</h3>
          <p class="sam-detect-related__card-outcome kpi-value">7 months advance tracking</p>
          <span class="sam-detect-related__card-link">Read story &rarr;</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/proof/belt-driven-assets-detection" class="sam-detect-related__card">
          <span class="sam-detect-related__card-industry">Chemicals</span>
          <h3 class="sam-detect-related__card-title">Belt-driven asset detections</h3>
          <p class="sam-detect-related__card-outcome kpi-value">Multiple fault detections</p>
          <span class="sam-detect-related__card-link">Read story &rarr;</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</main>
